0.body: JSEC is a revolutionary tool for Roblox developers, which allows quick and easy source-level obfuscation. It works by putting YOU in control, and you have ultimate control over what elements to protect. This guide will show you the powers of JSEC, and how to use them.
0.title: JSEC

16.body: JSEC allows for the manipulation of Control Flow, useful if you want to confuse people when they look at decompiled outputs of your script

21.body:
CF_START() local Player = game.Players.LocalPlayer local Humanoid = Player.Character.Humanoid if Humanoid.WalkSpeed > 16 then Player:Kick() elseif Humanoid.JumpPower > 50 then Player:Kick() end
CF_END()

22.body:
local function Get5Values(a) CF_START() local Return = {}; for i=1, 5 do -- Obviously could use a pairs loop however this is just to demonstrate the custom for loop CF generates Return[#Return+1] = a[i]; end; CF_END() return Return;
end

25.body: JSEC automatically protects all functions in your script, it will detect external environments trying to tamper with your functions.
25.title: Function Protection

3.body: Encrypts a string when protected, decrypts on runtime. <string> ENC_STR(<string>)
3.title: Encrypt String

4.body: Encrypts the global name, decrypts on runtime and grabs from the environment. <global> HIDE_GLOBAL(<global>)
4.title: Hide Global

5.body: Inserts some junk code at the location of where you called the macro. JUNK_CODE()
5.title: Junk Code

6.body: When JSEC compiles your script all instances of name will be replaced with value CMP_EXPR(<string name>, <string value>)
6.title: Compiler Expression

7.body: A secure varient of .FireServer, will attempt to anonymise the calling script. JSEC_FireServer(<RemoteEvent event>, ...<arguments>)
7.title: Protected FireServer

8.body: Will protect the inputted table against unknown environments calling __index. <table> PROTECT_TABLE(<table>)
8.title: Protect Table
